metadata.name: Disjoint and Disoriented #87
metadata.description:
Disjoint and Disoriented is about the abstract structure formed by the equalities and oppositions of its parts.

It might require high processing power depending on its features. A good desktop or laptop is recommended.

There are three render options available as url parameters in live mode:
- size=XXXX (up to 5760 pixels)
- texture=0 (disable canvas texture for print)
- shader=1 (use the shader throughout the painting process, can be heavy)

Created with p5.js and GLSL
dmarchi and lunarean, 2022.

metadata.name: Punktwelt #166
metadata.description:
Continuing on the theme of color perception in Farbteiler, Punktwelt is an exploration of color interaction, projection and perceived depth, and the aesthetics of simple Boolean operations on form.

Each shape is the result of a single block, a rectangular cuboid, subjected to a series of Boolean subtractions with other blocks, and rendered in parallel projection, oblique or axonometric, in the abstract landscape of the Punktwelt.

Some have horizons, some have banded or striped backgrounds. The unnatural drawing order and chromatic differences of the individual faces sometimes yields illusory or paradoxical visual geometries.

Press â€™sâ€™ to save a png. Press â€™4â€™ to export a high resolution png. Press â€™8â€™ to export a very high resolution png. Press â€™eâ€™ to export an SVG file (may take some time and produce large files).

Aspect ratio variations are 4:5, 5:4, 2:3, 3:2 and 1:1.

Built in Javascript with p5.js, p5.svg and csg.js.

metadata.name: VOYAGERS #74
metadata.description:
Generative animated painting made from looping gestures in a virtual void.

Voyagers is an exploration of automated gestures and screenspace layering effects. Each brush stroke sweeps through the canvas leaving a trail of color that either disappears or mixes with adjacent colors. The image slowly builds up to achieve an equilibrium between the rhythm of the gestures and the interaction of color values. These colors are quantized and dithered to produce chunky, textured, blocks of light that reify the materiality of the screen and the pixel. Two aspect ratios are possible, each with its own material relationship to screen-based work, 1:1 and 4:3 (vertical).

Press 's' to save looping animated GIF (live mode only).
Press 'p' to pause the animation.
Press 'c' to capture a single frame.
Made with P5.js and GLSL. By @galoandstuff.

metadata.name: RushGushBlush #161
metadata.description:
Let's celebrate #fxhashturnsone with a cascade of colors!

This is just my second release on fxhash and I couldn't be happier to dedicate this project, however simple, to this amazing community.

I could go on describing the details of this piece but honestly I just wanted to create something very colorful for the party, without putting too many hidden meanings! :)
(Or maybe not...)

Happy birthday fxhash!

---

80% of primary sales will be donated to the Processing Foundation and Save Pakistan.

---

There are 17 different palettes and 3 formats, hope you'll find a combination that makes you happy!
The texture might look weird in thumbnails, so I recommend opening the piece in full screen and/or download the png by pressing "s".

---

By Todemashi 2022

Made with p5js.
This project uses fx(stdio) by @alt_escapism - https://altesc.art/stdio

metadata.name: Uninhabitable #310
metadata.description:
Uninhabitable is a generative system built only from ellipses. The process of playing with different geometric and trigonometric disruptions gives rise to four different compositions which seek to evoque living constructions and environments. Besides the shape itself and its related distortion, the stroke weight of the lines plays a meaningful role in the piece. Following a discrete range [0.01,0.1,1] the weight reveals the process allowing the viewer to realize the trace of the huge amount of lines in each piece. This back and forth between scales and context is, while kind of stripping the code, part of my continuing interest on understanding the -usually- crazy paths of machines' way of thinking.

Press "h" to see it and high resolution and refresh to get back to the initial state. Press "h" to save it.

Uninhabitable is an original work by Iskra Velitchkova. 2021.

metadata.name: Annum #139
metadata.description:
This project is being released in celebration of the 1 year aniversary of Achromat, my first release on fxhash. In addition to being inspired by Achromat, aspects of other previous projects have been incorporated. My deepest gratitude to all who have collected my work over the past year.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

50% of primary sales go to Savepakistan.
